docs.lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — The Southwest has emerged as a key battleground for control of the United States Senate in the final days of the turbulent midterm election, with off-the-charts early voting numbers giving Democrats hope that they can win tight races in Arizona, Nevada and maybe, just maybe, the bank shot of them all, Texas.
